	(text "NOTE! The WS2812-2020-V6 that I'm using should be fine\nwithout the level shifting buffering. The datasheet says\nthat anything between 0.55*VDD and VDD+0.7 counts as high,\nso a 5V WS2812B can be happily driven by a 2.8V.\n\nBut I already added the buffer, so..."
		(exclude_from_sim no)
		(at 113.03 104.14 0)
		(effects
			(font
				(size 1.27 1.27)
			)
			(justify left)
		)
		(uuid "a25dd75b-da45-4b8f-829f-e2239fe63038")
	)
	(text "MIDI input and output.\n\nWe use the same 2-gate buffer chip both for the MIDI output and \nto buffer the 5V DIN signal for the WS2812B smart LED."
		(exclude_from_sim no)
		(at 179.832 174.244 0)
		(effects
